Package nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.roboflow

package nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.roboflow
This package provides the implementation of services responsible for interacting with the Roboflow API to send images and retrieve results. The services in this package handle various image processing tasks such as classification, segmentation, and object detection.

    ImageSenderOfRoboflow
    Implementation of the ImageSenderService for sending image frames to Roboflow for object detection and recognition.
    RoboflowService
    Service class for interacting with Roboflow-based workflows, including synchronous and asynchronous image processing.
    This class handles: Sending Base64-encoded images to the Roboflow API for inference. Processing responses to map predicted classes to appropriate ActionWithId or ObjectWithId entities. Storing predictions as SinglePrediction (or AbstractActionObservation for generalized usage). Testing pre-defined workflows via request calls, including describing the interface and running inferences.
    Key points:
    • Synchronous operations: RoboflowService.sendImg(String, String, String, String) immediately returns a list of predictions.
    • Asynchronous operations: RoboflowService.sendImgAsync(String, String, String, String) returns a CompletableFuture that completes once Roboflow returns its results.
    • Internal test methods (e.g., testPredefineWorkflowOnImage()) demonstrate usage of the Roboflow API for debugging or sample calls.

    Depends on:
    • RoboflowConfig for storing API credentials and relevant workflow information.
    • RequestSenderOfOKHttp for sending HTTP requests to Roboflow.
    • ObjectRepository and ActionRepository for looking up object/action names from the predicted class IDs.
